race.comment: DETECTIVE GUS (7) is a gelding by Frosted on debut for the Dabernig yard who are always worth keeping an eye on at Warrnambool. He's trialled well enough for this and can run a bold race first time out in a winnable maiden. SMASHING LAD (9) was narrowly beaten first up here over 1000m when getting within half a length of the winner. Up an extra 100m here suits ideally and he draws to effect. Looks a strong danger. PARIS WINDS (10) wasn't far away in a bunched finish on debut at Kilmore and is open to improvement. Drawn well and can figure. BANYAN JENNI (3) resumes and could be an improver this time in with Bates booked.
